The paper discusses the measure-theoretical fundamentals of cake-cutting, which is a problem in fair division and resource allocation. This topic is closely related to game theory (cs.GT) and algorithms (cs.DS), as well as artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and mathematical optimization (cs.MA). The paper also discusses continuity properties, which are relevant to the field of signal processing and analysis (cs.SI).
